rComments: Really horrible. Teaching algo requires a lot of patience and care. obviously his personality is up for that. He made fun of students who asked questions in class. No professor can be worse than him.

Arrogant! Doesn't teach properly.
This guy was absolutely shambolic in describing algorithms. I looked up rate my prof and actually swapped a course so I could fit into his lectures. To this day, I regret that choice. Very poor.
What a cool prof! He explains the materials very clearly and his class is so fun! Very knowledgeable and patient.

One of the best second year profs. He is very knowledgeable, funny, interesting, and clear. He will answer any question, and if you ever catch a mistake, he gives you money :D. But chances are you won't, he rarely makes any. He doesnt follow the textbook, so make sure to go to class and take notes (btw his notes are really good too).
Charming, interesting, funny, knowledgeable, and experienced. A wonderful lecturer and a very gracious man.

He teaches well in class... As everyone else have outlined, he is unapproachable, does not respect his students, and is just plain arrogant. A perfect example for any professor not to follow or be. He also imposes his own opinion without regards to how it affects OTHER sections of his course. His course has no homework/official book (GOOGLE)......

Excellent prof in class.  One of the best I've had at U of T (if not the best).  Trying to contact him out of class however, is nearly impossible.  He never responds to emails and the TAs for the class were some of the worst I've ever seen (extremely rude and dismissive).
Great professor, really explained everything very well.Not very approachable though

Good quality prof. Provides clear, interesting, and organized lectures in an awesome and extremely practical course. ECE299 is the most valuable 2nd year ECE course and he makes a huge contribution to this.

He is a good lecturer. He is intelligent and gives some very useful tips on structured programming....But the man is in love with himself...the very definition of narcissism and arrogance...very sarcastic...which makes it hard to approach him and ask questions...especially if there are 200 ppl in the classroom
